Here are the MSTest 3.x patterns for each scenario:

**1. Windows-only (registry)** — `[OSCondition]` (MSTest 3.10+):
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "Version", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(value);
}
```

**2. Skip in CI (local GPU)** — `[CICondition]`:
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void GpuRender_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    var result = GpuRenderer.Render(scene);
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

**3. Flaky external API** — `[Retry]` (MSTest 3.9+):
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast(TestContext testContext)
{
    var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(testContext.CancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
}
```
Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies — not to mask race conditions or shared state bugs.

**4. Temp file cleanup** — `[TestCleanup]` (runs even on failure):
```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class FileProcessorTests
{
    private string _tempFile = string.Empty;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void Process_WritesExpectedContent()
    {
        FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.AreEqual("expected", File.ReadAllText(_tempFile));
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

**Combining them** — attributes compose freely:
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
[Retry(2)]
public void WindowsGpu_WithFlakyDriver_ProducesOutput() { }
```

**Cleanup order reminder:** `[TestCleanup]` → `DisposeAsync` → `Dispose`, so cleanup always runs regardless of test outcome.
